    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-18T02:47:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-18T02:47:00-05:00" n="852"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d852">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Lot 55D128: Black Book, Tab 105: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief, Far East</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ridgway</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Joint Chiefs of
                            Staff</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-18T16:47:00+09:00">18
                            December 1951—4:47 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>C–59618. For info <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss> Adv 585.</p>
                <p>“Meeting opened 1100 on item 3. Hsieh referred to <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                        >UNC</gloss> insistence on rotation and replacement, and to his side’s
                    objection to ‘interference in internal affairs.’ <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                        >UNC</gloss> repeated position of rotation and replacement and airfields
                    from record of Dec 15. Hsieh stated the 2 questions above must be settled.
                        <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> asked if Hsieh had anything new to
                    propose. Hsieh replied no, insisted his side had made many concessions to <gloss
                        target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> views, it was <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                        >UNC</gloss>’s turn to make a move.</p>
                <p>“Recessed 1145. Continue tomorrow 1100. Signed Joy”.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
